Session of 2025
HOUSE BILL No. 2351
By Committee on Judiciary
Requested by Joe Molina on behalf of the Kansas Bar Association
2-7
1 AN ACT concerning arbitration; relating to contracts of insurance; making
2 certain agreements to appraise or arbitrate in contracts of insurance
3 invalid and creating exceptions therefor; amending K.S.A. 5-428 and
4 repealing the existing section.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 5-428 is hereby amended to read as follows: 5-428.
8 (a) (1) An agreement contained in a record to submit to arbitration any
9 existing or subsequent controversy arising between the parties to the
10 agreement is valid, enforceable and irrevocable, except upon a ground that
11 exists at law or in equity for the revocation of a contract, or as provided in
12 paragraph (2).
13 (2) An agreement contained in a contract of insurance entered into or
14 renewed after July, 1, 2025, to submit to appraisal or arbitration any
15 existing or subsequent controversy arising between the parties to the
16 agreement, except for those contracts between insurance companies,
17 including reinsurance contracts, shall not be valid, enforceable or
18 irrevocable, but shall be regarded as an offer by the insurance company to
19 enter into binding or nonbinding arbitration.
20 (b) The court shall decide whether an agreement to arbitrate exists or
21 a controversy is subject to an agreement to arbitrate.
22 (c) An arbitrator shall decide whether a condition precedent to
23 arbitrability has been fulfilled and whether a contract containing a valid
24 agreement to arbitrate is enforceable.
25 (d) If a party to a judicial proceeding challenges the existence of, or
26 claims that a controversy is not subject to, an agreement to arbitrate, the
27 arbitration proceeding may continue, pending final resolution of the issue
28 by the court, unless the court otherwise orders.
29 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 5-428 is hereby repealed.
30 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
31 publication in the statute book.

